Project Overview
Build a production-quality, single-page web application that replicates the core functionality of HumanSignal's Label Studio Enterprise. This is a data labeling and annotation platform used by ML/AI teams to create training datasets, evaluate model outputs, and manage human annotation workflows at scale.
The app should feel like a real product — polished UI, smooth interactions, proper state management, and a cohesive design system. Think of it as the tool a Search Relevance team at a food delivery company would use to evaluate whether vendor search results match user queries.

Tech Stack

Frontend: React (single-page app)
Styling: Tailwind CSS
State Management: React Context + useReducer (or Zustand if needed)
Routing: React Router v6
Icons: Lucide React
Data Persistence: localStorage (simulating a backend — no actual server needed)
ID Generation: crypto.randomUUID() or nanoid


Design System & Visual Identity
Follow these design principles closely — they match the real Label Studio aesthetic:
Color Palette

Primary brand: #FF8800 (warm orange — used for CTAs, active states, accent highlights)
Secondary: #4C5F7A (slate blue-gray — used for sidebar, headers)
Success/Complete: #2DB89A (teal green — progress bars, completed status)
Danger/Reject: #FF4D4F (red — cancel, reject, skip actions)
Warning: #FAAD14 (yellow — starred items, warnings)
Background: #FAFAFA for main content area, #FFFFFF for cards
Sidebar background: #F7F7F7 with subtle left border accents on active workspace
Text primary: #1A1A1A, secondary: #666666, muted: #999999

Typography

Font family: Inter (or system sans-serif fallback)
Headings use semibold/bold weight
Body text: 14px base, 13px for table cells and secondary info
Monospace for IDs, code snippets, and technical values

Component Patterns

Cards with subtle border: 1px solid #E8E8E8 and border-radius: 8px
Buttons: rounded-md, primary filled orange, secondary outlined
Tables: clean with light gray header backgrounds and hover row highlighting
Avatar circles: colored initials (e.g., green "JO", pink "MA") — 28px diameter
Progress bars: thin (4px height), teal fill on light gray track
Left colored borders on project cards (yellow, green, etc.) to indicate workspace color
Sidebar folders with colored folder icons matching workspace colors


