Key Interactions & Behaviors
Navigation

Clicking the HumanSignal logo or "Home" always returns to the dashboard
Breadcrumb navigation is fully clickable
Active page/tab is always visually highlighted

Data Manager

Column visibility is toggleable via the "Columns" dropdown
Clicking a task row in the Data Manager navigates to the Labeling Interface for that task
Bulk selection with checkboxes enables bulk actions
Tab views (Default, Max, Maria, Jorge) filter the task list by annotator — each tab remembers its own filter/sort state
"Label All Tasks" opens the labeling interface starting from the first unlabeled task

Labeling Interface

Left panel row click loads the task in the right panel without full page navigation
Keyboard shortcuts [1], [2], [3], [4] toggle the corresponding choice
Submit button saves the annotation and advances to the next task
Undo/redo cycle through annotation changes on the current task
The HTML content from task data is rendered in a sandboxed container (use dangerouslySetInnerHTML with a wrapper div, or an iframe for true isolation)

Project Settings

All settings changes are persisted immediately or on "Save" click
The Labeling Interface tab shows a live preview that updates as the config changes
Color picker is a simple row of circles — clicking one selects it with a checkmark or ring indicator

Project Creation Flow

"Create a Project" opens a modal or navigates to a creation form
Fields: Name, Description, Workspace (dropdown), Color
After creation, user is directed to the project's Settings > Labeling Interface to configure the template


What NOT to Build (Out of Scope)
Keep the scope manageable. Do NOT implement:

Actual backend server or API — use localStorage for all persistence
Real authentication / login flow — assume a logged-in user (JO/Jorge)
File upload / cloud storage integration
ML model backend or predictions
Real-time collaboration / WebSocket updates
SSO / SAML / LDAP
Export to YOLO, COCO, PASCAL VOC formats (just JSON export is fine)
Video, audio, image annotation tools (bounding boxes, polygons, etc.)
The "Generate with AI" labeling template feature (show the UI but it doesn't need to work)
Webhooks, Danger Zone settings (show the nav items but can show "Coming soon" content)


Implementation Priority
Build in this order:

App shell: Router, sidebar, top nav, design system components
Home Dashboard: Static layout with seed data
Projects View: Workspace sidebar + project grid + create project modal
Data Manager: Full table with columns, tabs, filters, sorting
Labeling Interface: Split panel, task rendering, annotation controls, submit flow
Project Settings: All tabs with General and Labeling Interface fully functional
Polish: Transitions, loading states, empty states, responsive adjustments


Quality Expectations

Zero TypeScript/lint errors
Responsive down to 1024px width minimum
Smooth transitions between pages (no jarring reloads)
Consistent spacing and alignment throughout
Empty states for all lists (when no projects, no tasks, etc.)
Proper cursor styles (pointer on clickable elements)
Keyboard accessible (Tab navigation, Enter to submit)
No lorem ipsum — all text should be realistic and contextual
